The paper discusses the use of latent variable models for statistical modeling of knowledge graphs, which is a common topic in the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also focuses on representation learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of knowledge graphs involves database management (cs.DB), and the semantic understanding of entities and relation-types involves natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
